title: Iowa State Men ranked 7th Nationally in preseason coaches poll
text:
Iowa State Men ranked 7th Nationally in preseason coaches poll Posted: Cyclones The latest news and information for the Iowa State University Cyclones sports teams, including football, basketball, volleyball, baseball, softball and more. More >> The latest news and information for the Iowa State University Cyclones sports teams, including football, basketball, volleyball, baseball, softball and more. More >> 
The mayor Fred Hoiberg may be gone but national expectations are still pretty high for the Iowa State men's basketball program under new head Steve Prohm. 
Iowa State is ranked number 7 in the nation in the first coaches poll released today. North Carolina which comes to cedar falls to play Northern Iowa in November is tied for number one with Kentucky. 
How good is the big 12 this year--- Cyclones are ranked in the top ten but only picked to finish third in the conference. 
With four starters returning from last year's Big 12 postseason tournament champions.. the Cyclones and head coach Steve Prohm believe they have the horses to make a run...
